{"title_page": "Chronicle Tower", "text_new": "{{Infobox building\n| image = Lexicon and Canaletto Towers, Islington, London.jpg\n| image_size = \n| name = Chronicle Tower (Lexicon Tower)\n| status = Complete\n| caption = \n| location = [[London]], {{postcode|EC|1}}<br>[[United Kingdom]]\n| coordinates = \n| roof = {{convert|115|m|ft|abbr=on}}\n| antenna_spire = \n| floor_count = 36\n| completion_date = May 2016\n| floor_area = \n| developer = [[Mount Anvil]]\n| architect = [[Skidmore Owings & Merrill]]\n| structural_engineer = \n| services_engineer = \n| other_designers = \n| main_contractor = \n| website =  [www.mountanvil.com/our-london-homes/lexicon/]\n}}\n\nThe '''Chronicle Tower''' (aka Lexicon Tower) is a 36-storey 115m tall residential building in [[City Road]], London, on the west side of the [[City Road Basin]], part of the [[Regent's Canal]]. The closest underground station is [[Angel tube station|Angel]].\n\nThe building includes 146 apartments<ref name=Mountanvil>{{cite web|title=Lexicon|url=http://www.mountanvil.com/our-london-homes/lexicon/|website=Mountanvil|accessdate=13 June 2015}}</ref> and is close to the [[City of London|\"Square Mile\"]] and \"[[Old Street Roundabout|Silicon Roundabout]]\".\n\nThe architects were [[Skidmore Owings & Merrill]] (SOM)<ref name=Mountanvil>{{cite web|title=Lexicon|url=http://www.mountanvil.com/our-london-homes/lexicon/|website=Mountanvil|accessdate=13 June 2015}}</ref> who also designed other notable buildings in the world including [[Willis Tower]] in [[Chicago]] and [[Burj Khalifa]] in [[Dubai]].\n\nThe building has an on-site gym, spa, swimming pool, and residents lounge.{{fact|date=June 2018}}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{coord|51.5300|-0.0970|display=title}}\n\n[[Category:Skyscrapers in the London Borough of Islington]]\n[[Category:Skidmore, Owings & Merrill buildings]]\n[[Category:Buildings and structures in the London Borough of Islington]]\n[[Category:Residential buildings completed in 2016]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox building\n| image = Lexicon and Canaletto Towers, Islington, London.jpg\n| image_size = \n| name = Chronicle Tower (Lexicon Tower)\n| status = Complete\n| caption = \n| location = [[London]], {{postcode|EC|1}}<br>[[United Kingdom]]\n| coordinates = \n| roof = {{convert|115|m|ft|abbr=on}}\n| antenna_spire = \n| floor_count = 36\n| completion_date = May 2016\n| floor_area = \n| developer = [[Mount Anvil]]\n| architect = [[Skidmore Owings & Merrill]]\n| structural_engineer = \n| services_engineer = \n| other_designers = \n| main_contractor = \n| website =  [www.mountanvil.com/our-london-homes/lexicon/]\n}}\n\nThe '''Chronicle Tower''' (aka Lexicon Tower) is a 36-storey 115m tall residential building in [[City Road]], London, on the west side of the [[City Road Basin]], part of the [[Regent's Canal]]. The closest underground station is [[Angel tube station|Angel]].\n\nThe building includes 146 apartments<ref name=Mountanvil>{{cite web|title=Lexicon|url=http://www.mountanvil.com/our-london-homes/lexicon/|website=Mountanvil|accessdate=13 June 2015}}</ref> and is close to the [[City of London|\"Square Mile\"]] and \"[[Old Street Roundabout|Silicon Roundabout]]\".\n\nThe architects were [[Skidmore Owings & Merrill]] (SOM).<ref name=Mountanvil>{{cite web|title=Lexicon|url=http://www.mountanvil.com/our-london-homes/lexicon/|website=Mountanvil|accessdate=13 June 2015}}</ref>.\n\nThe building has an on-site gym, spa, swimming pool, and residents lounge.{{fact|date=June 2018}}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{coord|51.5300|-0.0970|display=title}}\n\n[[Category:Skyscrapers in the London Borough of Islington]]\n[[Category:Skidmore, Owings & Merrill buildings]]\n[[Category:Buildings and structures in the London Borough of Islington]]\n[[Category:Residential buildings completed in 2016]]\n", "name_user": "Londonarchitecture", "label": "safe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Chronicle_Tower"}
{"title_page": "Hello, My Twenties! 2", "text_new": "{{short description|2017 South Korea TV series}}\n{{Infobox television\n| show_name                = Hello, My Twenties! 2\n| image                    = Age_of_Youth_2_Promotional_Poster.jpg\n| caption                  = Promotional poster featuring girls of Belle Epoque\n| show_name_2              = \n| genre                    = [[Youth]] <br> [[Drama (modern genre)|Drama]] <br> [[Romance film|Romance]]\n| writer                   = Park Yeon-seon\n| director                 = {{ill|Lee Tae-gon (director)|ko|\uc774\ud0dc\uace4 (\uc5f0\ucd9c)|lt=Lee Tae-gon}}\n| creative_director        = \n| starring                 = [[Han Ye-ri]]<br/>[[Han Seung-yeon]]<br/>[[Park Eun-bin]]<br/>[[Ji Woo]]<br>Choi Ah-ra\n| theme_music_composer     = \n| opentheme                = \n| endtheme                 = \n| composer                 = \n| country                  = South Korea\n| language                 = Korean\n| num_seasons              =\n| num_episodes             = 14\n| executive_producer       = Choi Hyuk-jin<br>Ham Young-hoon<br>Park Joon-seo\n| producer                 = Choi Jae-suk\n| editor                   = \n| cinematography           = \n| runtime                  = \n| company                  = Take 2 Media Group{{efn|A subsidiary of {{illm|GnG Production|ko|\uc9c0\uc564\uc9c0\ud504\ub85c\ub355\uc158}}}}<br>Drama House\n| distributor              = [[JTBC]]\n| network                  = [[JTBC]]\n| picture_format           = [[1080i]] ([[HDTV]]) \n| audio_format             = [[Dolby Digital]] \n| first_run                = South Korea\n| first_aired              = {{Start date|2017|08|25}}\n| last_aired               = {{End date|2017|10|07}}\n| preceded_by              = ''[[Hello, My Twenties!]]''\n| website                  = http://tv.jtbc.joins.com/youth2\n| website_title            = \n| production_website       = \n| production_website_title = \n}}\n\n'''''Hello, My Twenties! 2'''''<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.jtbcworldwide.com/script/detail?pgmMstSeq=307|title=Hello, My Twenties! 2|website=JTBC Worldwide|publisher=JTBC Content Hub|accessdate=February 10, 2018}}</ref> ({{ko-hhrm|\uccad\ucd98\uc2dc\ub3002|\u9751\u6625\u6642\u4ee32|Cheongchunsidae 2|Ch'\u014fngch'unsidae 2|lit='''''Age of Youth 2'''''}}) is a [[Korean drama|South Korean television series]] starring [[Han Ye-ri]], [[Han Seung-yeon]], [[Park Eun-bin]], [[Ji Woo]] and Choi Ah-ra. It is the sequel to the 2016 series ''[[Hello, My Twenties!]]''.<ref>{{Cite news|author=Kang Seo-jeong|title=[Oh!\uc388 \ucd08\uc810] '\uccad\ucd98\uc2dc\ub3002', \ud55c\uc608\ub9ac\u00b7\ubc15\ud61c\uc218\u00b7\ub958\ud654\uc601\u00b7\ubc15\uc740\ube48\u00b7\ud55c\uc2b9\uc5f0 \ub610 \ubb49\uce60\uae4c|url=http://osen.mt.co.kr/article/G1110586243|work=OSEN|date=February 16, 2017|accessdate=February 16, 2017|language=ko}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|author=Lee Da-won|script-title=ko:[\ub2e8\ub3c5] '\uccad\ucd98\uc2dc\ub300' \uc2dc\uc98c2, \uc81c\uc791 \ud655\uc815\u2026\ud55c\uc608\ub9ac\ubd80\ud130 \ubc15\uc740\ube48\uae4c\uc9c0 \uc758\ub9ac\ub85c \ubb49\uce5c\ub2e4|url=http://sports.khan.co.kr/entertainment/sk_index.html?cat=view&art_id=201702161429013&sec_id=540201|work=[[Kyunghyang Shinmun|Sports Kyunghyang]]|date=February 16, 2017|accessdate=February 16, 2017|language=ko}}</ref> The series aired on cable network [[JTBC]] on Fridays and Saturdays at 23:00 ([[Korea Standard Time|KST]])<ref>{{cite web|author=Park Ki-young|url=http://osen.mt.co.kr/article/G1110631110|script-title=ko:[\uacf5\uc2dd\uc785\uc7a5] JTBC \"'\uccad\ucd98\uc2dc\ub3002', '\ud488\uc704\ub140' \ud6c4\uc18d \ud655\uc815..8\uc6d4 \ubc29\uc1a1\"|trans-title=[Official] JTBC \"'Age of Youth' to air after 'Woman of Dignity'... August broadcast\"|work=OSEN|date=April 22, 2017|accessdate=May 4, 2017|language=ko}}</ref> for 14 episodes from August 25 to October 7, 2017.<ref>{{cite web|author=C. Oh|url=https://www.soompi.com/2017/07/25/watch-age-youth-2-teaser-helps-viewers-reminisce-characters-return-belle-epoque/|title=Watch: \"Age Of Youth 2\" Teaser Helps Viewers Reminisce As Characters Return To The Belle Epoque|work=OSEN|date=July 25, 2017|accessdate=July 25, 2017|language=en}}</ref>\n\n==Synopsis==\nA slice-of-life story about five college students who connect over the growing pains in their youth.\n\n== Introduction ==\nIn our lives we are hurt in a relationship. However, the relationship cannot be avoided.\n\nBut there is one strange thing.\n\nI have a lot of memories of wounds I have received from others, but I have no memories of the wounds I have given to others.\n\nIn short, the demand and supply of \"shuttle\" do not match.\n\nMaybe it's caused by more unintended injuries.\n\nMaybe there are people who hurt others in their own existence.\n\nMaybe the memory of the wound I got was a self-inflicted scratch.\n\nA three-member family waits for the signal in front of the crosswalk.\n\nThe man and woman with a seven-year-old girl in the middle are laughing hahaha.\n\nSomeone who rush into a secondhand bookstore as if to avoid them.\n\nI don't know what to do because I can't get rid of myself. Maybe it's because of that. A book that's been pushed out from the inside of the book is falling off. a pink letter found in the book\n\nOn the back of the letter is the address of Belle Epoque.\n\nJo Eun, who will be her new housemate, goes to Belle Epoque with her letter.\n\n==Cast==\n\n===Main cast (Belle Epoque)===\n*[[Han Ye-ri]] as Yoon Jin-myung \u2013 29-years-old\n*[[Han Seung-yeon]] as Jung Ye-eun \u2013 23-years-old\n*[[Park Eun-bin]] as Song Ji-won \u2013 23-years-old\n*[[Ji Woo]] as Yoo Eun-jae \u2013 21-years-old\n*[[Choi Ara]] as Jo Eun \u2013 21-years-old\n\n===The men around the Belle Epoque===\n*[[Kim Min-seok (actor)|Kim Min-seok]] as Seo Jang-hoon\n:deputy of the share house, Belle Epoque's owner, Joeun's love interest\n*[[Son Seung-won]] as Im Sung-min\n:Ji-won's friend from college newspaper.\n*[[Shin Hyun-soo]] as Yoon Jong-yeol\n:Eun-jae's ex-boyfriend.\n*[[Lee Yoo-jin (actor)|Lee Yoo-jin]] as Kwon Ho-chang  \n:Ye-eun's love interest; an engineering student who knows nothing about dating.\n*[[An Woo-yeon]] as Heimdall / Lee Jin-kwang\n:A member of an idol group Asgard who is five years into his debut, but yet to reach stardom.\n\n===Others===\n*Shin Se-hwi as Ahn Ye-ji\n:Jo Eun's friend\n*[[Choi Bae-young]] as Song Kyung-ah\n:Jung Ye-eun's friend\n*[[Ha Eun-seol]] as Han Yoo-kyung\n:Jung Ye-eun's friend\n* [[Jo Byung-gyu]] as Jo Chung-han\n*[[Go Min-si]] as Oh Ha-na\n\n===Cameo appearances===\n*[[Ryu Hwa-young]] as Kang Yi-na<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.mydaily.co.kr/new_yk/html/read.php?newsid=201703161618629640&ext=na|title=[MD\uc778\ud130\ubdf0] '\uccad\ucd98\uc2dc\ub3002' PD\uac00 \ubc1d\ud78c #\ub958\ud654\uc601 \ud2b9\ubcc4\ucd9c\uc5f0 #\uc0c8\uba64\ubc84 #\ub17c\ub780|work=My Daily|date=March 16, 2017|language=ko}}</ref>\n*[[Yoon Park]] as Park Jae-wan<ref name=\"Seoul Economy Daily 1\">{{cite web|url=http://www.sedaily.com/NewsView/1OJSS6V1Z7|script-title=ko:'\uccad\ucd98\uc2dc\ub3002' \uce21 \"\uc2dc\uc98c1 3\uac1c\uc6d4 \ud6c4 \uc774\uc57c\uae30\ub85c \uc2dc\uc791\u2026\ub958\ud654\uc601\u00b7\uc724\ubc15 \ud2b9\ubcc4\ucd9c\uc5f0\"|work=Seoul Economy Daily|date=August 18, 2017|language=ko}}</ref>\n*[[Ji Il-joo]] as Go Doo-young<ref name=\"Seoul Economy Daily 1\" />\n*[[Pentagon (South Korean band)|PENTAGON]] as members of idol group Asgard<ref>{{cite web|url=http://sports.chosun.com/news/ntype.htm?id=201708140100122790008969&servicedate=20170813|script-title=ko:[\ub2e8\ub3c5]\ud39c\ud0c0\uace4, '\uccad\ucd98\uc2dc\ub3002' \ucd9c\uc5f0\u2026\uc548\uc6b0\uc5f0\uacfc \uc544\uc774\ub3cc \uadf8\ub8f9 \uacb0\uc131|work=Chosun|date=August 13, 2017|language=Korean}}</ref> \n**[[Jinho]] as Baldr / Choi Jin-ho\n**Shinwon as Ur / Kim Shin-won\n**[[Yeo One]] as Tyr / Shin Chang-goo\n**Yuto as Odin\n**[[Kino (entertainer)|Kino]] as Freyr\n**[[Wooseok]] as Thor / Park Woo-seok \n*[[Ace (South Korean band)|A.C.E]] as members of idol group The Fifth Column<ref>{{cite web|url=http://sports.donga.com/3/all/20170901/86120714/1|title=A.C.E, '\uccad\ucd98\uc2dc\ub3002' \uce74\uba54\uc624 \ucd9c\uc5f0\u2026\uc5f0\uae30\ub3cc \ub3c4\uc804[\uacf5\uc2dd]|work=Sports Donga|date=September 1, 2017|language=Korean}}</ref>\n*[[Z.Hera]]\n\n==Production==\n* Originally, it was expected that all five main roles would be the same from the previous season. However, early on [[Ryu Hwa-young]] was removed from the main cast.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.dramabeans.com/2017/03/cast-changes-and-a-new-character-for-age-of-youth-season-2/|title=Cast changes and a new character for Age of Youth Season 2 \u00bb Dramabeans Korean drama recaps|date=2017-03-17|work=Dramabeans|access-date=2017-08-25|language=en-US}}</ref> Instead a new character, Jo Eun, was created to fill in the five person dynamic of the show. [[Park Hye-soo]] was also supposed to be part of the main cast, but due to a scheduling conflict, she stepped down from the role. Unlike Ryu Hwa-young, this happened late into pre-production and so the character, Yoo Eun-jae, stayed and the role was taken on by actress [[Ji Woo]] instead.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.soompi.com/2017/06/06/age-youth-2-reveals-newest-additions-main-cast-park-hye-soo-drops/|title=\"Age Of Youth 2\" Reveals Newest Additions To Main Cast, Park Hye Soo Drops Out|last=6|first=D. Kim June|last2=2017|date=2017-06-06|website=Soompi|access-date=2017-08-25}}</ref>\n* [[Onew]] was originally cast in the role of Kwon Ho-chang, but he stepped down in light of controversy surrounding him ten days before the drama's premiere, and was replaced with [[Lee Yoo-jin (actor)|Lee Yoo-jin]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://tvdaily.asiae.co.kr/read.php3?aid=15028512641268127002|title=SM \"\uc628\uc720, \uc81c\uc791\uc9c4\uacfc \uc0c1\uc758 \ub05d\uc5d0 '\uccad\ucd98\uc2dc\ub3002' \ud558\ucc28\" [\uacf5\uc2dd\uc785\uc7a5]|date=August 16, 2017|website=TV Daily|language=ko}}</ref>\n\n==Ratings==\n* In this table, {{color|blue|'''the blue numbers'''}} represent the lowest ratings and {{color|red|'''the red numbers'''}} represent the highest ratings.\n* '''N/A''' denotes that the rating is not known.\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n|-\n! rowspan=\"3\" |{{abbr|Ep.|Episode}}\n! rowspan=\"3\" |Original broadcast date\n! rowspan=\"3\" |Title\n! colspan=\"3\" |Average audience share\n|-\n! colspan=\"2\" |AGB Nielsen<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.nielsenkorea.co.kr/tv_terrestrial_day.asp?menu=Tit_1&sub_menu=2_1&area=00|title=Nielsen Korea|work=AGB Nielsen Media Research|language=Korean|access-date=August 25, 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170513095904/http://www.nielsenkorea.co.kr/tv_terrestrial_day.asp?menu=Tit_1&sub_menu=3_1|archive-date=May 13, 2017|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n! TNmS<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.tnms.tv/rating/default.asp?menu=Cable_Daily|title=TNmS Ratings|website=TNmS|language=Korean|access-date=August 25, 2017}}</ref>\n|-\n! Nationwide\n! [[Seoul Capital Area|Seoul]]\n! Nationwide\n|-\n! 1\n| August 25, 2017\n| ''I'm Upset By Small Things #Us''<br/>(\ub098\ub294 \uc791\uc740 \uac83\uc5d0 \uc5f4 \ubc1b\ub294\ub2e4 #\uc6b0\ub9ac\ub4e4)\n| 2.228%\n| {{color|blue|'''1.995%'''}}\n| 2.5%\n|-\n! 2\n| August 26, 2017\n| ''I'm a Coward #Stranger'' <br/>(\ub098\ub294 \uac81\uc7c1\uc774\ub2e4 #\uc774\ubc29\uc778)\n| 2.405%\n| 2.341%\n| 2.9%\n|-\n! 3\n| September 1, 2017\n| ''I Decided to Hate You #Crime and Punishment''<br/>(\ub098\ub294 \ub110 \ubbf8\uc6cc\ud558\uae30\ub85c \ub9c8\uc74c\uba39\uc5c8\ub2e4 #\uc8c4\uc640\ubc8c)\n| {{color|blue|'''1.657%'''}}\n| {{N/A}}\n| {{color|blue|'''1.7%'''}}\n|-\n!4\n| September 2, 2017\n| ''I Survived #Selfish Gene''<br/>(\ub098\ub294 \uc0b4\uc544\ub0a8\uc558\ub2e4 #\uc774\uae30\uc801 \uc720\uc804\uc790)\n| 2.431%\n| 2.256%\n| 3.1%\n|-\n! 5\n| September 8, 2017\n| ''My Heart is As Fickle As a Reed #First Love''<br/>(\ub098\ub29