 \n | lowest attendance          =\n | average attendance         =\n | prevseason                 = [[1938\u201339 Divizia B|1938\u201339]]\n | nextseason                 = [[1940\u201341 Divizia B|1940\u201341]]\n}}\n\nThe '''1939\u201340 [[Divizia B]]''' was the sixth season of the second tier of the [[Romanian football league system]].\n\nThe format has been maintained, four series of 10 teams. The winners of the series were supposed to promote in the [[Liga I|Divizia A]], but the winners of the 3rd and 4th series were not promoted from different reasons. Also 3rd and 4th place from the first series and the sixth place from the second series were promoted to fill the vacant places from Divizia A.<ref>[http://www.rsssf.com/tablesr/roem2hist.html#40 rsssf.com]</ref><ref>[http://www.romaniansoccer.ro/divizia_b/tables/1939_40.shtml romaniansoccer.ro]</ref>\n\n== Team changes ==\n{{col-begin|width=auto}}\n{{col-2}}\n\n===To Divizia B===\n'''Promoted from [[1938\u201339 Divizia C|Divizia C]]'''\n* [[Astra-Metrom Bra\u0219ov]]\n* [[CFR Turnu Severin]]\n* [[Cimentul Turda]]\n* [[Electrica Timi\u0219oara]]\n* [[Feroemail Ploie\u0219ti]]\n* [[Maccabi Chi\u0219in\u0103u]]\n* [[CSA Aurul Brad|Mica Brad]]\n* [[Muncitorul Cern\u0103u\u021bi]]\n* [[Oltul Sf\u00e2ntu Gheorghe]]\n* [[Sparta Media\u0219]]\n* [[SS Doc Gala\u021bi]]\n* [[CS Muncitorul Re\u0219i\u021ba|SSM Re\u0219i\u021ba]]\n\n'''Relegated from [[1938\u201339 Divizia A|Divizia A]]'''\n* [[Chinezul Timi\u0219oara]]\n* [[FC Ploie\u0219ti|Tricolor Ploie\u0219ti]]\n* [[CS Gloria Arad|Gloria Arad]]\n{{col-break|gap=5em}}\n\n===From Divizia B===\n'''Relegated to [[1939\u201340 Divizia C|Divizia C]]'''\n* [[AS CFR Bra\u0219ov|CFR Bra\u0219ov]]\n* [[Luceaf\u0103rul Bucure\u0219ti (interwar)|Luceaf\u0103rul Bucure\u0219ti]]\n* [[Hatmanul Luca Arbore Rad\u0103u\u021bi]]\n* [[FC Unirea Alba Iulia|Unirea MV Alba Iulia]]\n* [[Societatea Gimnastic\u0103 Sibiu|SG Sibiu]]\n* [[FC Carmen Bucure\u0219ti|Mociorni\u021ba Col\u021bea Bucure\u0219ti]]\n* [[Jahn Cern\u0103u\u021bi]]\n* [[\u0218oimii Sibiu]]\n* [[Tricolor Baia Mare]]\n\n'''Promoted to [[1939\u201340 Divizia A|Divizia A]]'''\n* [[CAM Timi\u0219oara]]\n* [[Unirea Tricolor Bucure\u0219ti]]\n* [[Gloria CFR Gala\u021bi]]\n{{col-end}}\n\n===Renamed teams===\nDacia Unirea Br\u0103ila was renamed as [[ACS Dacia Unirea Br\u0103ila|FC Br\u0103ila]].\n\nMonopol T\u00e2rgu Mure\u0219 was renamed as [[Monopol T\u00e2rgu Mure\u0219|CS T\u00e2rgu Mure\u0219]].\n\nSporting Chi\u0219in\u0103u was renamed as [[Sporting Chi\u0219in\u0103u|Nistru Chi\u0219in\u0103u]].<ref>[https://blogulcudoigalbeni.wordpress.com/2012/02/19/fotbalul-din-basarabia-in-perioada-interbelica/ Fotbalul din Basarabia \u00een perioada interbelic\u0103]. blogulcudoigalbeni.wordpress.com {{in lang|ro}}</ref>\n\n===Disqualified teams===\n[[Mihai Viteazul Chi\u0219in\u0103u]] and Textila Moldova Ia\u0219i were disqualified.\n\n===Other teams===\nCraiovan Craiova and Rovine Grivi\u021ba Craiova merged, the new formed team was named [[FC Craiova]].<ref>[http://www.cvlpress.ro/07.09.2018/fc-craiova-o-campioana-in-anii-de-razboi/ FC Craiova \u2013 o campioan\u0103 \u201e\u00een anii de r\u0103zboi\u201d]. cvlpress.ro {{in lang|ro}}</ref>\n\n==League tables==\n\n=== Serie I ===\n{{#invoke:Sports table|main|style=WDL\n|source=[http://www.romaniansoccer.ro/divizia_b/tables/1939_40.shtml romaniansoccer.ro]\n\n<!--Team positions-->\n|team1=PLO |team2=MUR |team3=CRA |team4=BR\u0102 |team5=CAO |team6=CTA\n|team7=DVC |team8=NIS |team9=AMB |team10=VIC\n\n<!-- Team qualifications here (defined below)-->\n|result1=DA\n|result3=DA\n|result4=DA\n|result9=R\n|result10=R\n\n<!--Team results here-->\n|update=30 June 1940\n|win_PLO= 13|draw_PLO= 2|loss_PLO= 3|gf_PLO= 68|ga_PLO= 15 <!-- Ploie\u0219ti -->\n|win_MUR= 12|draw_MUR= 2|loss_MUR= 4|gf_MUR= 56|ga_MUR= 26 <!-- Mure\u0219ul T\u00e2rgu Mure\u0219 -->\n|win_CRA= 12|draw_CRA= 2|loss_CRA= 4|gf_CRA= 41|ga_CRA= 22 <!-- Craiova -->\n|win_BR\u0102= 11|d