|Olimpia CFR Satu Mare]]\n|name_TGM = [[Monopol T\u00e2rgu Mure\u0219|CS T\u00e2rgu Mure\u0219]]\n|name_CAR = [[Victoria Carei]]\n\n|hth_CRI=''Cri\u0219ana Oradea'' was not promoted. On 30 August 1940 the [[Second Vienna Award]] was signed and territory of [[Northern Transylvania]] <br /> was assigned from [[Romania]] to [[Hungary]], including [[Oradea]].\n|hth_UCJ=''Universitatea Cluj'' was promoted instead of Cri\u0219ana Oradea. Even that the [[Second Vienna Award]] regard also [[Cluj-Napoca]] in the territory <br /> of [[Northern Transylvania]], Universitatea Cluj refused to play in [[Hungary]] and relocated to [[Sibiu]].\n|hth_CAR=''Victoria Carei'' withdrew at the start of the second half and lost the remaining 9 matches with 0-3.\n\n<!--Status-->\n|status_CRI=C\n|status_UCJ=P\n|status_CAR=R\n\n<!--Table settings and rules-->\n|winpoints=2\n|show_limit=7\n|class_rules=Rules for classification: 1) Points 2) Head-to-head points; 3) Head-to-head goal difference; 4) Head-to-head goals scored; 5) Head-to-head away goals scored; 6) Goal difference; 7) Goals scored.\n\n<!--Qualification and relegation column definitions-->\n|res_col_header=Q\n|col_DA=green1 |text_DA= Promotion to [[1940\u201341 Divizia A|Divizia A]]\n|col_R=red1    |text_R= Relegation to [[1940\u201341 Divizia C|Divizia C]]\n}}\n\n=== Serie IV ===\n{{#invoke:Sports table|main|style=WDL\n|source=[http://www.romaniansoccer.ro/divizia_b/tables/1939_40.shtml romaniansoccer.ro]\n\n<!--Team positions-->\n|team1=FRB |team2=FER |team3=MAC |team4=PRA |team5=DVA |team6=MCH\n|team7=TUR |team8=MUN |team9=SSD |team10=TRA\n\n<!-- Team qualifications here (defined below)-->\n|result1=DA\n|result9=R\n|result10=R\n\n<!--Team results here-->\n|update=30 June 1940\n|win_FRB= 15|draw_FRB= 2|loss_FRB= 1|gf_FRB= 69|ga_FRB= 20 <!-- Franco-Rom\u00e2na Br\u0103ila -->\n|win_FER= 13|draw_FER= 3|loss_FER= 2|gf_FER= 65|ga_FER= 16 <!-- Feroemail Ploie\u0219ti -->\n|win_MAC= 12|draw_MAC= 2|loss_MAC= 4|gf_MAC= 58|ga_MAC= 13 <!-- Maccabi Bucure\u0219ti -->\n|win_PRA=  9|draw_PRA= 3|loss_PRA= 6|gf_PRA= 37|ga_PRA= 35 <!-- Prahova Ploie\u0219ti -->\n|win_DVA=  9|draw_DVA= 2|loss_DVA= 7|gf_DVA= 44|ga_DVA= 42 <!-- Dacia VA Gala\u021bi -->\n|win_MCH=  7|draw_MCH= 2|loss_MCH= 9|gf_MCH= 30|ga_MCH= 42 <!-- Maccabi Chi\u0219in\u0103u -->\n|win_TUR=  6|draw_TUR= 3|loss_TUR= 9|gf_TUR= 32|ga_TUR= 33 <!-- Turda Bucure\u0219ti -->\n|win_MUN=  6|draw_MUN= 1|loss_MUN=11|gf_MUN= 26|ga_MUN= 53 <!-- Muncitorul Cern\u0103u\u021bi -->\n|win_SSD=  3|draw_SSD= 0|loss_SSD=15|gf_SSD= 19|ga_SSD= 70 <!-- SS Doc Gala\u021bi -->\n|win_TRA=  1|draw_TRA= 0|loss_TRA=17|gf_TRA=  9|ga_TRA= 65 <!-- Traian Tighina -->\n\n<!--Team definitions (wikilinks in table)-->\n|name_FRB = [[Franco-Rom\u00e2na Br\u0103ila]]\n|name_FER = [[Feroemail Ploie\u0219ti]]\n|name_MAC = [[Maccabi Bucure\u0219ti]]\n|name_PRA = [[Prahova Ploie\u0219ti]]\n|name_DVA = [[Dacia Vasile Alecsandri Gala\u021bi|Dacia VA Gala\u021bi]]\n|name_MCH = [[Maccabi Chi\u0219in\u0103u]]\n|name_TUR = [[Turda Bucure\u0219ti]]\n|name_MUN = [[Muncitorul Cern\u0103u\u021bi]]\n|name_SSD = [[SS Doc Gala\u021bi]]\n|name_TRA = [[Traian Tighina]]\n\n<!--Status-->\n|status_FRB=C\n|status_SSD=R\n|status_TRA=R\n\n<!--Table settings and rules-->\n|winpoints=2\n|show_limit=7\n|class_rules=Rules for classification: 1) Points 2) Head-to-head points; 3) Head-to-head goal difference; 4) Head-to-head goals scored; 5) Head-to-head away goals scored; 6) Goal difference; 7) Goals scored.\n\n<!--Qualification and relegation column definitions-->\n|res_col_header=Q\n|col_DA=green1 |text_DA= Promotion to [[1940\u201341 Divizia A|Divizia A]]\n|col_R=red1    |text_R= Relegation to [[1940\u201341 Divizia C|Divizia C]]\n}}\n\n== See also ==\n* [[1939\u201340 Divizia A]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n{{Liga II seasons}}\n<!--{{1939\u201340 in Romanian football}}-->\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:1939-40 Divizia B}}\n[[Category:Liga II seasons]]\n[[Category:1939\u201340 in European second tier association footbal